{
  "texts": [
    "Over the past few decades, epistemologists have devoted a great deal of attention to questions concerning epistemic autonomy.",
    "Inquiries in this area have considered the nature of epistemic autonomy (Carter, 2020; Elgin, 2021; Encabo, 2008; Grasswick, 2018; King, 2021; Matheson & Lougheed, 2021; Zagzebski, 2012) and whether epistemic autonomy is a worthy ideal (Ahlstrom-Vij, 2013, Chapter 4; Battaly, 2021; Coady, 2002; Dellsén, 2021; Hardwig, 1985; Matheson, 2022; Roberts and Jay Wood, 2007).",
    "Very plausibly, whether epistemic autonomy has value depends on how it is defined.",
    "To determine whether the impact of ADDs on epistemic autonomy is a cause for concern, it will first be necessary to consider whether there is a valuable form of epistemic autonomy.",
    "To begin, consider some recent proposals as to the nature of epistemic autonomy."
  ]
}